problem_prompt: Solve the following problem. Compute $35^{1723} - 16^{1723}$ modulo 6.
solution: Note that, modulo 6, $35 \equiv -1$ and $16 \equiv 4$. Therefore, $35^{1723} - 16^{1723} \equiv (-1)^{1723} - 4^{1723} \equiv -1 - 4^{1723}$. Note that $4^2 \equiv 4$ modulo 6, so $-1 - 4^{1723} \equiv -1 - 4 \equiv -5 \equiv \boxed{1}$ modulo 6.
gpt_response:
We know that any number raised to the power of an even number is congruent to 1 modulo 6, and any number raised to the power of an odd number is congruent to itself modulo 6.

Therefore, $35^{1723}$ is congruent to $5^{1723}$ modulo 6, which is congruent to 5 since 1723 is an odd number.

Similarly, $16^{1723}$ is congruent to $4^{1723}$ modulo 6, which is congruent to 4 since 1723 is an odd number.

Therefore, $35^{1723} - 16^{1723}$ is congruent to $5 - 4 = 1$ modulo 6.

So, $35^{1723} - 16^{1723} \equiv 1 \pmod{6}$.
